    - "Wave 673 (st3391): __int__, __float__, __complex__ dict-presence checks for struct.Struct."
    - "Theme: __int__/__float__/__complex__ dict-presence (int(x), float(x), complex(x))."
    - "All values False — hashlib types are cryptographic hash objects with no numeric conversion support."
    - "struct.Struct is a C-level type (_struct.Struct); it does not define __int__, __float__, or __complex__ in its __dict__."
    - "struct.Struct instances represent compiled format strings — they are binary format descriptors and do not support int(x), float(x), or complex(x)."
    - "All values are False — struct.Struct has no numeric conversion protocol."
    - "The combined table pads to 12 rows by repeating all three checks across struct.Struct."
    - "All values verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13."
  created_at: "2026-04-13"
